"An normal eye means this eye have no signs of cataract"
A mature cataract is a cataract that has developed to an advanced stage, where the lens of the eye is opaque and dense, and vision is severely impaired.
An immature cataract is an early stage of a clouding of the eyes lens that can cause vision problems.
